results.name: Number of primes between n-th prime and n-th composite or number of primes that are >=Min[prime(n),c(n)] and are < Max[prime(n),c(n)].
example: n=4: in range {p(4)=11 and c(4)=10} 1 prime was found, a(4)=1; n=25: in range {p(25)=97 and c(25)=38} 13 primes, {41,43,..,97} were found, so a(25)=13.
results.author: _Labos Elemer_, Jul 31 2002
